    <body>
        <p MadCap:conditions="Products.Capture">Converts the cursor to Text Rectangle mode, which lets you create a square or rectangle shape with text by clicking in the <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Capture">image</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.MovieSync">frame</MadCap:conditionalText> and dragging in any direction. When you release the cursor, default text is shown in a popup editor. You can replace the text with your own and click outside the area to see the finished shape. In addition, this mode adds a background to the box (as opposed to a transparent background), which makes it easier to see the text. </p>
        <p MadCap:conditions="Products.Mimic">Converts the cursor to Text Rectangle mode, which lets you create a square or rectangle shape with text by clicking in the frame and dragging in any direction. Double-click in the rectangle to type text, and click outside the area to see the finished shape.</p>
